The paper deals with ensemble selection for consensus clustering, which is a problem in machine learning. The paper proposes a method for selecting a subset of partitions from a large ensemble based on diversity and frequency. This involves techniques from areas such as machine learning, data mining, and computational linguistics. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DM (Data Mining). The paper also involves clustering and classification, which are covered in sub-categories such as cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
